titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Michael Ginsberg Books Records
titlestmt.author: by Michael Rush

repository.corpname: Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library

did.abstract: The records of Michael Ginsberg Books includes financial records, catalogs, catalog cards, and appraisal records. Financial records consist of accounts, invoices, ledgers, receipts, checks, and statements. Catalogs include both inventory catalogs and lists of recent aquisitions from Michael Ginsberg Books as well as catalogs from other rare book dealers. Catalog cards record inventory items, the bulk of which are numbered sequentially. Appraisal records include notes, correspondence, and other papers related to appraisals conducted by Michael Ginsberg.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.
Box 118 (computer disks): Restricted Fragile Material. Reference copies may be requested. Consult Access Services for further information.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The Michael Ginsberg Books Records is the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Michael Ginsberg Books Records. Yale Collection of Western Americana, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Collections are processed to a variety of levels, depending on the work necessary to make them usable, their perceived research value, the availability of staff, competing priorities, and whether or not further accruals are expected. The library attempts to provide a basic level of preservation and access for all collections [as they are acquired], and does more extensive processing of higher priority collections as time and resources permit.
This collection received a basic level of processing, including rehousing and minimal organization.

Information included in the Description of Papers note and Collection Contents section is drawn from information supplied with the collection and from an initial survey of the contents. Folder titles appearing in the contents list below are often based on those provided by the creator or previous custodian. Titles have not been verified against the contents of the folders in all cases. Otherwise, folder titles are supplied by staff during initial processing.
This finding aid may be updated periodically to account for new acquisitions to the collection and/or revisions in arrangement and description.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records of Michael Ginsberg Books includes financial records, catalogs, catalog cards, and appraisal records. Financial records consist of accounts, invoices, ledgers, receipts, checks, and statements. Catalogs include both inventory catalogs and lists of recent aquisitions from Michael Ginsberg Books as well as catalogs from other rare book dealers. Catalog cards record inventory items, the bulk of which are numbered sequentially. Appraisal records include notes, correspondence, and other papers related to appraisals conducted by Michael Ginsberg.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: I. Financial Records, 1974-2004. II. Catalogs, 1975-2007. III. Catalog Cards. IV. Appraisal Records, 1980s-1990s.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Financial records consist of accounts, invoices, ledgers, receipts, checks, and statements. In most cases descriptions and date information were transcribed from boxes as received.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Catalogs are arranged in rough chronological order.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Catalogs include both inventory catalogs and lists of recent aquisitions from Michael Ginsberg Books as well as catalogs from other rare book dealers, including William Reese Co.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Catalog cards are organized into two groups: numbered cards, which are arranged in numerical order, and unnmbered cards, which were filed in an alphabetical sequence.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Catalog cards record item-level information about books, manuscripts, and other items in the inventory of Michael Ginsberg Books.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Appraisal records include notes, correspondence, and other papers related to appraisals conducted by Michael Ginsberg. The bulk of the appraisal records relate to the William Russell Jazz Collection at the Historic New Orleans Collection.
